<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 2:58PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northeastern Appomattox and western Buckingham Counties through 330
PM EDT...
At 257 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wingina, or 7 miles north of Bent Creek, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible. Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this
storm and may lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your
vehicle through flooded roadways.
Locations impacted include...
Buckingham...
Bent Creek...
Wingina...
Toga...
and Tower Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
